lavery%20will%20break%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20his%20now-defunct%20magazine%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%202011.%20The%20opinion%20piece%20was%20authored%20by%20Aala%20Fazili%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20scholar%20who%20has%20also%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20and%20senior%20advocate%20P.N.%20Raina%20said%20that%20the%20court%20quashed%20the%20charges%20under%20Sections%2018%20(terror%20conspiracy)%20and%20121%20(waging%20war%20against%20the%20country)%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20and%20153-B%20(imputations%2C%20assertions%20prejudicial%20to%20national-integration)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20against%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20(Shah)%20will%20face%20trial%20under%20Section%2013%20(abetting%20unlawful%20activities)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20and%20Sections%2035%20(receiving%20foreign%20funds%20illegally)%20and%2039%20(offences%20by%20companies)%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raina%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20filed%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20at%20the%20CIJ%20police%20station%20in%20Jammu%20on%20April%204%2C%202022%20(FIR%20No%3A%2001%2F2022)%2C%20around%2011%20years%20after%20Fazili%E2%80%99s%20piece%20appeared%20in%20the%20magazine.%20A%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20case%20last%20year%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%20this%20year%2C%20the%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffahad-shah-public-safety-act-jammu-kashmir-high-court%5C%22%3Ehad%20quashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA)%20invoked%20against%20Shah%20by%20terming%20the%20allegations%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmere%20surmise%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cvague%20and%20bald%20assertions%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20accused%20the%20authorities%20of%20snatching%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20and%20legal%20rights%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnestyusa.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F04%2Fasa200012011en_11.pdf%5C%22%3EAmnesty%20International%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20PSA%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Clawless%20law%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20has%20been%20used%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Crevolving%20door%E2%80%9D%20policy%20for%20suspects%20against%20whom%20the%20government%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20little%20or%20no%20evidence%20to%20bring%20formal%20charges%20against%20them%20in%20the%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20PSA%20dossier%2C%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfilled%20with%20hatred%20against%20%5Bthe%5D%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpromoted%20separatism%E2%80%9D.%20It%20further%20alleged%20that%20his%20%E2%80%9Cactivities%20seem%20to%20be%20prejudicial%20to%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20security%2C%20integrity%2C%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20of%20the%20UT%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20also%20the%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dossier%20also%20accused%20Shah%20of%20arranging%20%E2%80%9Clogistical%20support%20for%20anti-national%20activities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cinciting%20violence%20thereby%20leading%20to%20disturbance%20in%20public%20order%E2%80%9D%20while%20terming%20him%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthreat%20to%20public%20order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20court%20quashed%20the%20PSA%20proceedings%20against%20him%2C%20Shah%20was%20arrested%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20in%20the%20case%20in%20which%20he%20has%20now%20been%20granted%20bail.%20He%20has%20been%20granted%20bail%20in%20three%20other%20criminal%20cases%20brought%20against%20him%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20for%20the%20reporting%20done%20by%20his%20magazine%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20was%20charged%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20May%202020%20over%20the%20coverage%20of%20a%20gun%20battle%20between%20militants%20and%20security%20forces%20in%20Srinagar.%20In%20the%20encounter%E2%80%99s%20aftermath%2C%20local%20residents%20had%20alleged%20that%20security%20forces%20took%20away%20their%20precious%20belongings%2C%20a%20charge%20denied%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegations%20and%20the%20denial%20were%20widely%20reported%20by%20local%20and%20national%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20on%20January%2030%2C%202021%2C%20Shah%20was%20booked%20under%20Sections%20153%20(provocation%20with%20intent%20to%20cause%20riot)%20and%20505%20(statements%20conducive%20to%20public%20mischief)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20for%20a%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20alleged%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpressuring%E2%80%9D%20the%20management%20of%20a%20private%20school%20in%20Shopian%20to%20organise%20the%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20had%20denied%20the%20charge%20and%20proceeded%20to%20file%20a%20criminal%20case%20against%20Shah%2C%20who%20was%20later%20granted%20bail%20by%20a%20court.%20Shah%20has%20reportedly%20faced%20six%20cases%20of%20intimidation%20between%20June%202017%20and%20January%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20case%20pertains%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20coverage%20of%20a%20gun%20battle%20in%20south%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Pulwama%20district%20in%20which%20three%20militants%2C%20including%20a%20top%20commander%2C%20were%20gunned%20down%20last%20year.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%9Cglorifying%20terrorist%20activities%E2%80%9D%20and%20causing%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%20against%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%20by%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cincorrect%20reporting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2019%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20pulled%20down%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20website%20under%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Information%20and%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20a%20controversial%20law%20which%20has%20been%20criticised%20by%20the%20free%20speech%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPress%20freedom%20in%20India%20has%20suffered%20relentless%20blows%20in%20recent%20years%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%E2%80%99s%20latest%20report%2C%20India%20slipped%20to%20161%20out%20of%20180%20countries%20this%20year%2C%20losing%2011%20more%20spots%20as%20compared%20to%20the%202022%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Paris-based%20press%20freedom%20watchdog%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%2C%20India%20has%20been%20using%20%E2%80%9Ccharges%20of%20defamation%2C%20sedition%2C%20contempt%20of%20court%20and%20endangering%20national%20security%20%E2%80%A6%20increasingly%20..%20against%20journalists%20critical%20of%20the%20government%2C%20who%20are%20branded%20as%20%E2%80%98anti-national%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20has%20denied%20these%20charges%2C%20accusing%20the%20watchdog%20of%20%E2%80%9Csubverting%20the%20democratic%20freedoms%20all%20over%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700293259000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12194450%2Fimage-44.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fafter-nearly-2-years-jk-hc-grants-bail-to-kashmir-walla-editor-fahad-shah%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shah%20was%20held%20on%20charges%20of%20terrorism%20for%20publishing%20the%20article%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20shackles%20of%20slavery%20will%20break%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20his%20now-defunct%20magazine%2C%20'The%20Kashmir%20Walla%2C'%20in%202011.%20The%20opinion%20piece%20was%20authored%20by%20Aala%20Fazili%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20scholar%20who%20has%20also%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20case.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fafter-nearly-2-years-jk-hc-grants-bail-to-kashmir-walla-editor-fahad-shah%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BBlood%20Money%26quot%3B%20Only%20Way%20To%20Save%20Kerala%20Nurse%20On%20Death%20Row%20In%20Yemen%3A%20Lawyer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20way%20to%20save%20the%20nurse%20from%20Kerala%20on%20death%20row%20in%20Yemen%20is%20to%20negotiate%20a%20%26quot%3Bblood%20money%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20family%20of%20the%20victim%2C%20said%20the%20lawyer%20who%20has%20requested%20a%20Delhi%20court%20to%20allow%20her%20mother%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENimisha%20Priya%20faces%20death%20sentence%20for%20the%20murder%20of%20a%20Yemeni%20national%20and%20their%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20dismissed%20her%20appeal.%20A%20direct%20negotiation%20with%20the%20victim's%20family%20now%20remains%20the%20only%20way%20ahead%20under%20the%20Shariah%20law%20prevalent%20in%20Yemen%2C%20said%20lawyer%20Subhash%20Chandran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20isn't%20as%20simple%20as%20it%20sounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20travel%20ban%20to%20Yemen%20since%202016%20due%20to%20which%20Indian%20citizens%20cannot%20visit%20Yemen%20without%20the%20permission%20of%20the%20Indian%20government.%20So%20we%20are%20not%20able%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20victim's%20family%20for%20the%20blood%20money%20negotiation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Chandran%2C%20who%20is%20part%20of%20the%20forum%20comprising%20politicians%2C%20businessmen%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20expatriates%20seeking%20justice%20for%20Nimisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBlood%20money%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20compensation%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20victim's%20family%20to%20secure%20her%20release.%20But%20for%20this%20negotiation%2C%20it's%20important%20for%20her%20mother%20to%20travel%20to%20Yemen%20and%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20urged%20the%20centre%20to%20decide%20within%20a%20week%20on%20the%20request%20from%20her%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENimisha's%20mother%2C%20who%20works%20as%20a%20house%20help%20for%20a%20family%20in%20Kochi%2C%20has%20sold%20her%20property%20to%20fight%20the%20case%2C%20said%20Mr%20Chandran%2C%20adding%20that%20several%20activists%20and%20expatriates%20formed%20the%20Nimisha%20Priya%20International%20Action%20Council%20in%202023%20to%20ensure%20she%20gets%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forum%20is%20now%20requesting%20the%20central%20government%20and%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20to%20negotiate%20with%20the%20victim's%20family.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20ready%20to%20pay%2C%20but%20considering%20the%20political%20situation%20in%20Yemen%2C%20the%20government%20is%20the%20appropriate%20authority%20for%20the%20negotiation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'He%20Abused%20Her%2C%20Tortured%20Her'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENimisha%20was%20convicted%20of%20killing%20Talal%20Abdo%20Mahdi%20after%20she%20injected%20him%20with%20sedatives%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20retrieve%20her%20passport%20from%20his%20possession.%20She%20remains%20in%20a%20Yemeni%20jail%20since%20the%202017%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202017%2C%20internal%20conflict%20began%20in%20Yemen%20and%20her%20husband%20and%20child%20had%20returned%20to%20India.%20She%20was%20alone%20that%20time%20when%20her%20sponsor%20started%20abusing%20and%20torturing%20her%20physically%20and%20financially.%20He%20had%20confiscated%20her%20passport%20and%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20escape%20from%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Chandran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20get%20her%20passport%20back%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20sedate%20him%20but%20an%20overdose%20led%20to%20his%20death.%20That%20was%20the%20time%20of%20an%20internal%20conflict%20in%20Yemen%20and%20she%20did%20not%20get%20proper%20legal%20defence.%20Sanaa%2C%20the%20city%20where%20was%20she%20underwent%20trial%2C%2