ved%20to%20be%20a%20complete%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-killer-whales-orcas-attack-sink-boats-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Trites%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Marine%20Mammal%20Research%20Unit%20at%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20using%20brash%20and%20blaring%20tunes%20to%20avoid%20orcas%20could%20help%20the%20whale%20find%20the%20boats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInitially%2C%20the%20playing%20of%20loud%20sounds%20underwater%20might%20mask%20the%20signature%20sounds%20of%20sailboats%20%E2%80%94%20but%20ultimately%20the%20whales%20would%20catch%20on%20and%20use%20it%20to%20more%20easily%20locate%20vessels%20playing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Trites%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrites%20also%20explained%20that%20orcas%20can%20hear%20at%20higher%20frequencies%20than%20humans%2C%20meaning%20that%20trying%20to%20cover%20up%20the%20sounds%20of%20sailboats%20that%20the%20orcas%20have%20come%20to%20recognize%20is%20a%20futile%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20practice%20is%20not%20encouraged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20way%20heavy%20metal%2C%20or%20any%20music%2C%20could%20be%20effective%20at%20discouraging%20orcas%20from%20approaching%20boats%20is%20if%20it%20were%20played%20so%20loud%20that%20it%20hurts%20the%20animal%20and%20causes%20hearing%20loss%2C%20Trites%20said.%20(Needless%20to%20say%2C%20humans%20should%20not%20do%20this.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Trites%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20if%20sailors%20adopted%20this%20method%2C%20the%20most%20harmful%20result%20would%20be%20an%20addition%20to%20noise%20pollution%20in%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20blasting%20music%20underwater%20of%20any%20kind%20is%20that%20it%20is%20ultimately%20just%20adding%20more%20noise%20pollution%20to%20the%20ocean%20which%20can%20have%20detrimental%20effects%20on%20other%20marine%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Trites%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoise%20pollution%20is%20already%20a%20major%20issue%20for%20marine%20animals%20that%20rely%20on%20sound%20to%20attract%20mates%2C%20communicate%20with%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20track%20food%20sources%2C%20avoid%20predators%2C%20and%20navigate%20the%20ocean%2C%20according%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Ffacts%2Focean-noise.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eto%20NOAA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sound%20travels%20more%20quickly%20and%20much%20further%20in%20water%20than%20it%20does%20through%20air%2C%20making%20it%20a%20useful%20tool%20for%20underwater%20species%2C%20scientists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aba4658%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20noted.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuman-caused%20noise%20pollution%20comes%20from%20a%20variety%20of%20sources%2C%20including%20ships%2C%20energy%20production%20via%20wind%20turbines%2C%20underwater%20mining%2C%20and%20even%20low-flying%20planes.%20Anthropogenic%20climate%20change%20is%20also%20affecting%20underwater%20soundscapes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aba4658%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%20shows%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20scientists%20are%20still%20unsure%20how%20to%20stop%20the%20Iberian%20orca%20population%20from%20ramming%20into%20boats%2C%20but%20experts%20say%20there%20are%20a%20variety%20of%20methods%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forca-killer-whale-attack-boat-expert-advice-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ekeep%20sailors%20safe%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20these%20encounters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20methods%20include%3A%20avoiding%20orcas%20or%20keeping%20a%20distance%20when%20spotted%2C%20de-powering%20the%20boat%20and%20dropping%20sails%2C%20maintaining%20a%20low%20profile%20as%20they%20approach%20the%20boat%2C%20keeping%20a%20firm%20grip%20on%20the%20boat%20in%20case%20they%20do%20ram%20into%20the%20vessel%2C%20and%20waiting%20until%20the%20orcas%20leave%20the%20area%20until%20sailing%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20the%20jury%20is%20still%20out%20assessing%20exactly%20what%20is%20going%20on%2C%20and%20what%20can%20be%20done%20(if%20anything)%20to%20stop%20this%20adherent%20targeting%20of%20sailboats%20by%20this%20small%20group%20of%20killer%20whales%2C%26quot%3B%20Trites%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20a%20passing%20fad%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20going%20to%20take%20a%20coordinated%20effort%20by%20orca%20specialists%20and%20mariners%20to%20experimentally%20try%20different%20deterrence%20methods%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20is%20going%20to%20ultimately%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheavy-metal-music-deter-orcas-ramming-sailboat-iberian-coast-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700290130000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65584b5c22cf74a57399cc0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheavy-metal-music-deter-orcas-ramming-sailboat-iberian-coast-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20music%20will%20also%20add%20to%20human-made%20ocean%20noise%2C%20which%20is%20already%20a%20major%20issue%20for%20marine%20animals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CHannah%20Getahun)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A109%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheavy-metal-music-deter-orcas-ramming-sailboat-iberian-coast-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IMF%20revises%20Pakistan's%20foreign%20loan%20requirement%20to%20USD%2025%20billion%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700289502000%2C%22visual