0which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20provides%20for%20%E2%80%9Cany%20information%E2%80%9D%20that%20is%20given%20electronically%20as%20oral%20evidence%2C%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20tasked%20with%20examining%20the%20proposed%20legislation%2C%20has%20recommended%20the%20deletion%20of%20these%20words%2C%20saying%20that%20this%20could%20cause%20serious%20complications%20in%20its%20interpretations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20cautioned%20against%20the%20tampering%20of%20evidence%20and%20recommended%20%E2%80%9Csafeguarding%20the%20authenticity%20and%20integrity%20of%20electronic%20and%20digital%20records%20acquired%20during%20the%20course%20of%20investigation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201870)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20(which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973)%2C%20was%20referred%20to%20the%2031-member%20committee%20after%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%2011%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%5C%22%3Eadopted%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20report%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20dissent%20notes%2C%20opposition%20MPs%20have%20criticised%20these%20Bills%20for%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Ccopy-paste%E2%80%9D%20legislations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20flagged%20drafting%20errors%20and%20the%20haste%20with%20which%20they%20are%20being%20pushed%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20analyses%20the%20main%20recommendations%20of%20the%20committee%20report%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20information%E2%80%9D%20given%20electronically%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FBHARATIYA_SAKSHYA_BILL%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20defines%20evidence%20as%20oral%20and%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOral%20evidence%20includes%20%E2%80%9Cstatements%20or%20any%20information%20given%20electronically%20which%20the%20court%20permits%20or%20requires%20to%20be%20made%20before%20it%20by%20witnesses%20in%20relation%20to%20matters%20of%20fact%20under%20inquiry%20and%20such%20statements%20or%20information%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20it%20defines%20documentary%20evidence%20as%20documents%2C%20%E2%80%9Cincluding%20electronic%20or%20digital%20records%20produced%20for%20the%20inspection%20of%20the%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdocuments%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20expanded%20to%20include%20electronic%20or%20digital%20records%20on%20emails%2C%20server%20logs%2C%20documents%20on%20computers%2C%20laptop%20or%20smartphone%2C%20messages%2C%20websites%2C%20locational%20evidence%20and%20voice%20mail%20messages%20stored%20on%20digital%20devices.%20The%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cevidence%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20expanded%20to%20include%20any%20information%20given%20electronically%2C%20which%20will%20enable%20the%20appearance%20of%20witnesses%2C%20accused%2C%20experts%20and%20victims%20through%20electronic%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FSC_Report_Bharatiya_Sakshya_Bill_2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20it%20was%20brought%20to%20its%20attention%20during%20deliberations%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cany%20information%E2%80%9D%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20evidence%20could%20cause%20serious%20complications%20in%20its%20interpretations%2C%20and%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%E2%80%9D%20is%20different%20from%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cany%20information%E2%80%9D%20be%20deleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20opines%20that%20inclusion%20of%20%E2%80%98any%20information%E2%80%99%20along%20with%20%E2%80%98statement%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20same%20line%20may%20cause%20complications%20in%20its%20interpretation.%20The%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20that%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98any%20information%E2%80%99%20may%20be%20deleted%20in%20this%20clause%20to%20avoid%20such%20complications%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fno-handcuffs-for-economic-offences-safeguards-electronic-evidence-misuse-parl-panel-report-on-bns%5C%22%3ENo%20Handcuffs%20for%20Economic%20Offences%2C%20Digital%20Evidence%20%E2%80%98Safeguards%E2%80%99%3A%20Parliamentary%20Panel%20Report%20on%20BNSS%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESafeguarding%20electronic%20and%20digital%20evidence%20against%20tampering%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20the%20need%20to%20safeguard%20the%20authenticity%20of%20electronic%20and%20digital%20records%20acquired%20during%20investigation%20against%20tampering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20Clause%2057%20provides%20for%20treating%20electronic%20and%20digital%20records%20produced%20from%20proper%20custody%20as%20primary%20evidence%2C%20but%20does%20not%20mention%20about%20ensuring%20proper%20chain%20of%20custody%20of%20such%20digital%20and%20electronic%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20provision%20of%20maintaining%20proper%20chain%20of%20custody%20has%20already%20been%20incorporated%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20criminal%20laws%20in%20developed%20countries%20such%20as%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%20(USA)%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20(UK).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20recommended%20that%20that%20proper%20chain%20of%20custody%20needs%20to%20be%20maintained%20to%20avoid%20tampering%20during%20the%20handling%20of%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20safeguarding%20the%20authenticity%20and%20integrity%20of%20electronic%20and%20digital%20records%20acquired%20during%20the%20course%20of%20investigation%20is%20crucial%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20evidences%20are%20prone%20to%20tampering%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20takes%20into%20account%20the%20suggestion%20submitted%20before%20the%20committee%20and%20recommends%20that%20a%20provision%20may%20be%20inserted%20to%20mandate%20that%20all%20electronic%20and%20digital%20records%20acquired%20as%20evidence%20during%20the%20course%20of%20investigation%20are%20securely%20handled%20and%20processed%20through%20proper%20chain%20of%20custody.%20Appropriate%20provision%20in%20this%20regard%20may%20be%20made%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%2C%202023.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-gender-neutrality-section-377-criminalising-adultery%5C%22%3EIn%20%E2%80%98Interest%20of%20Gender%20Neutrality%E2%80%99%2C%20Parl%20Panel%20Recommends%20Keeping%20Section%20377%2C%20Criminalising%20Adultery%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrafting%20and%20cross-referencing%20errors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20also%20noted%20a%20number%20of%20drafting%20errors%20in%20various%20clauses%20and%20recommended%20their%20rectifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20several%20cross-referencing%20errors%20in%20different%20clauses%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20also%20undertook%20a%20detailed%20examination%20of%20the%20text%20of%20each%20clause%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20Bill%20contains%20some%20cross-referencing%20errors.%20The%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20the%20ministry%20to%20rectify%20such%20errors%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20concluded%20that%20the%20changes%20brought%20in%20the%20Bill%20would%20%E2%80%9Creflect%20the%20growing%20importance%20of%20digital%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20more%20comprehensive%20legal%20framework%20in%20line%20with%2021st%20century%20technological%20advancements%20and%20societal%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20recommendations%20on%20the%20other%20two%20Bills%20can%20be%20read%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-gender-neutrality-section-377-criminalising-adultery%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fno-handcuffs-for-economic-offences-safeguards-electronic-evidence-misuse-parl-panel-report-on-bns%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700286898000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18112028%2Fimage-1517.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-parl-panel-said-on-bharatiya-sakshya-bill-which-seeks-to-replace-the-indian-evidence-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20has%20recommended%20deleting%20the%20words%20'any%20information'%20to%20avoid%20any%20misinterpretations%2C%20concerning