20was%20named%C2%A0%26quot%3BSendero%20del%20Cangrejo%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BTrail%20of%20the%20Crabs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EClusters%20of%20white%20crabs%20on%20the%20ocean%20floor%20helped%20lead%20scientists%20to%20a%20new%20discovery%20off%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgalapagos-giant-tortoise-thought-extinct-100-years-has-been-found-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGal%C3%A1pagos%20Islands%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20a%20field%20of%20hydrothermal%20vents%2C%20or%20deep-sea%20hot%20springs%2C%20full%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20were%20on%20an%20expedition%20with%20the%20nonprofit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fschmidtocean.org%2Fsquat-lobsters-guide-scientists-to-new-hydrothermal-vent-field%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESchmidt%20Ocean%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20August%20to%20September%20in%20search%20of%20as%20yet%20unexplored%20hydrothermal%20vents.%20Hydrothermal%20vents%2C%20which%20were%20first%20discovered%20in%201977%20east%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-on-the-galpagos-islands-according-to-frequent-visitor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGal%C3%A1pagos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20create%20chemosynthetic%20ecosystems%20that%20support%20life%20in%20places%20that%20are%20mostly%20barren.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20crushing%20darkness%20of%20the%20deep%20sea%2C%20life%20thrives%20on%20these%20vents%20as%20bacteria%20facilitate%20a%20whole%20food%20web%20by%20converting%20chemicals%2C%20rather%20than%20sunlight%2C%20into%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Schmidt%20Ocean%20Institute.%20%26quot%3BHydrothermal%20vents%20threw%20open%20the%20door%20to%20new%20scientific%20possibilities%20and%20have%20been%20found%20and%20explored%20across%20the%20Ocean%20for%20decades.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Purple%20and%20orange%20chimneys%20and%20geologic%20structures%20on%20the%20ocean%20floor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557fe3c36d588dc55d2d178%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStunning%20chimneys%20and%20geologic%20structures%20formed%20by%20hydrothermal%20venting.%20Iguanas%20Vent%20Field%2C%20Galapagos%20Islands.%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20Ocean%20Institute%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20greyish%20white%20vent%20chimney%20on%20the%20sea%20floor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557fe7a22cf74a57399c7f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221620%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20vent%20chimney%20discovered%20within%20a%20previously%20unknown%20hydrothermal%20vent%20field%20near%20the%20Gal%C3%A1pagos%20Islands.%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20Ocean%20Institute%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20expedition%20was%20in%20search%20of%20vents%20that%20scientists%20had%20suspected%20existed%20since%20the%20early%202000s%20but%20were%20difficult%20to%20locate.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20our%20team%20of%20chemists%2C%20geologists%2C%20biologists%2C%20and%20a%20few%20crabs%20to%20find%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Roxanne%20Beinart%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Rhode%20Island%20who%20co-led%20the%20expedition%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20of%20scientists%20was%20surveying%20the%20sea%20floor%20with%20an%20underwater%20robot%20when%20they%20finally%20spotted%20a%20Galatheid%20crab%2C%20also%20known%20as%20a%20squat%20lobster%2C%20a%20crustacean%20that%20is%20more%20closely%20related%20to%20hermit%20crabs%20than%20the%20American%20lobster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crabs%20are%20known%20to%20live%20near%20hydrothermal%20vents%2C%20so%20the%20team%20followed%20them%2C%20with%20the%20density%20of%20crabs%20growing%20thicker%20and%20thicker%20until%20they%20finally%20arrived%20at%20the%20hydrothermal%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20did%20feel%20like%20the%20squat%20lobsters%20were%20leading%20us%20like%20breadcrumbs%2C%20like%20we%20were%20Hansel%20and%20Gretel%2C%20to%20the%20actual%20vent%20site%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20scientists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cluster%20of%20white%20and%20red%20riftia%20tube%20worm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557ff2322cf74a57399c829%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221620%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20large%20cluster%20of%20riftia%20tube%20worms%20proved%20the%20researchers%20were%20unquestionably%20in%20a%20new%20hydrothermal%20vent%20field.%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20Ocean%20Institute%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hydrothermal%20vent%20field%2C%20larger%20than%20a%20professional%20soccer%20field%2C%20was%20made%20up%20of%20%26quot%3Bfive%20geyser-like%20chimneys%20and%20three%20hot%20springs%2C%20like%20those%20you%20might%20see%20in%20Yellowstone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20said.%20The%20hottest%20water%20temperature%20recorded%20at%20the%20site%20was%20550%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERicardo%20Visaira%20Coronel%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-baby-tortoises-galapagos-airport-hidden-in-suitcase-2021%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGal%C3%A1pagos%20National%20Park%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Dennisse%20Maldonado%20of%20INOCAR%2C%20who%20are%20both%20Ecuadorian%20and%20were%20on%20the%20ship%2C%20named%20the%20vent%20field%20%26quot%3BSendero%20del%20Cangrejo%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BTrail%20of%20the%20Crabs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20found%20a%20large%20cluster%20of%20giant%20tube%20worms%20and%20collected%20other%20specimens%2C%20some%20of%20which%20may%20be%20entirely%20new%20species%2C%20the%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStuart%20Banks%2C%20senior%20marine%20scientist%20at%20the%20Charles%20Darwin%20Foundation%2C%20said