a%20previous%20lower%20court%20order%20that%20allowed%20Adani%20to%20block%20authorities%20from%20collecting%20evidence%20from%20Singapore.%E2%80%9D%20DRI%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20company%20%5Bhas%5D%20thwarted%20%5Bthe%20move%20to%20share%20documents%20with%20authorities%5D%20for%20years%2C%20as%20per%20the%20news%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdani%20has%20denied%20wrongdoing%2C%20and%20told%20%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20had%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20cooperated%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20authorities%20by%20providing%20details%20and%20documents%20sought%20more%20than%20four%20years%20ago%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20deficiency%20or%20objection%E2%80%9D%20was%20communicated%20by%20investigators%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20that%20ahead%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%202024%20election%2C%20political%20opponents%20have%20increased%20pressure%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20administration%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20favouritism%20toward%20Adani%20in%20government%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CModi%20and%20Adani%2C%20who%20both%20hail%20from%20Gujarat%2C%20have%20denied%20impropriety%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fmodi-adani-oligarchy-stock-offshore%5C%22%3EThe%20Undeniable%20Rise%20of%20Oligarchic%20Capitalism%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOver-invoicing%20Imports%20%3D%20Consumers%20Overpaying%20for%20Electricity%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadani-coal-imports-over-pricing-customers-overcharged-fuel-ft%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520detailed%2520FT%2520investigation%2520points%2Chidden%2520shareholder%2520in%2520Adani%2520firms.%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20according%20to%20data%20obtained%20from%20customs%20records%2C%20that%20the%20Adani%20Group%2C%20%E2%80%9Cappears%20to%20have%20imported%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20coal%20at%20prices%20well%20above%20market%20value.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdata%20supports%20longstanding%20allegations%20that%20Adani%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20private%20coal%20importer%2C%20has%20been%20inflating%20fuel%20costs%20and%20led%20millions%20of%20Indian%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20to%20overpay%20for%20electricity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20London-based%20broadsheet%20examined%20data%20between%202019%20and%202021%2C%20and%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9CAdani%20used%20offshore%20intermediaries%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20Dubai%20and%20Singapore%20to%20import%20%245%20billion-worth%20of%20coal%20at%20prices%20that%20were%20at%20times%20more%20than%20double%20the%20market%20price.%E2%80%9D%20It%20cited%20journeys%20of%20coal%2C%20during%20which%20the%20price%20of%20coal%2C%20%E2%80%9Cunaccountably%20increased%20by%20over%20%2470%20million.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20report%20again%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20coal%20imports%20over-pricing%20allegations%20which%20had%20been%20dogging%20the%20Adanis%20despite%20denials.%20The%20Opposition%20Congress%20party%20alleged%20that%20the%20Adani%20group%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fadani-group-likely-overbilled-coal-consumers-by-12000-crore-congress%2Farticle67417527.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20behind%20the%20biggest%20scam%20modern%20India%20has%20seen.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20They%20cited%20the%20fresh%20revelations%2C%20reported%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20to%20indicate%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20than%20Rs%2012%2C000%20crore%20may%20have%20been%20siphoned%20out%20of%20the%20country%20in%20two%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20general%20secretary%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20claimed%20that%20this%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20a%20metaphorical%20loot%20but%20literally%20theft%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20pockets%20of%20crores%20of%20Indians.%20He%20said%20the%20latest%20revelations%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20examined%2030%20Adani%20coal%20shipments%20between%202019%20and%202021%20amounting%20to%203.1%20million%20tonnes%2C%20found%20a%2052%25%20profit%20even%20on%20a%20low%20margin%20business%20like%20coal%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGujarat%20Police%20%E2%80%98summons%E2%80%99%20journalists%20reporting%20on%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20coal%20irregularities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20consistently%20denied%20charges%20that%20there%20is%20any%20personal%20friendship%20or%20connection%20between%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%20that%20have%20allowed%20Adani%20to%20grow%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20any%20conglomerate%20has%20in%20recent%20times%20and%20managed%20to%20control%20large%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20India.%20But%20Gujarat%20police%E2%80%99s%20enthusiasm%20in%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%98summon%E2%80%99%20journalists%20who%20are%20reporting%20on%20allegations%20of%20impropriety%20in%20how%20the%20Adani%20Group%20functions%20have%20only%20added%20grist%20to%20the%20mill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20on%20Friday%20(November%2010)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-grants-financial-times-journalists-interim-protection-from-gujarat-police-arrest-over-article-against-adani-group-242062%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Supreme%2520Court%2520on%2520Friday%2CAugust%2520against%2520the%2520Adani%2520group.%5C%22%3Eto%20grant%20%E2%80%9Cinterim%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20coercive%20action%20to%20two%20journalists%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0Benjamin%20Nicholas%20Brooke%20Parkin%20and%20Chloe%20Nina%20Cornish%2C%20who%20have%20been%20summoned%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20Police%20in%20relation%20to%20an%20article%20